# Performance Optimization Guidelines

## Bundle Size Targets

Keep shared routes and reusable components light. Prefer route-level splitting for heavy screens and avoid importing large dependencies into common modules.

## Code Splitting

### Route-Level Lazy Loading

```typescript
import { lazy, Suspense } from "react";

// ✅ CORRECT: Lazy load heavy components
const AttendanceBoard = lazy(
  () => import("@/features/attendance/AttendanceBoard")
);

export default function AttendancePage() {
  return (
    <Suspense fallback={<LoadingFallback />}>
      <AttendanceBoard />
    </Suspense>
  );
}
```

### Component-Level Splitting

```typescript
// Only for very large, conditionally-rendered components
const HeavyModal = lazy(() => import("./HeavyModal"));

{
  showModal && (
    <Suspense fallback={<ModalSkeleton />}>
      <HeavyModal />
    </Suspense>
  );
}
```

## React Query Optimization

### Caching Strategy

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Appropriate stale times
export function usePatients() {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["patients"],
    queryFn: getPatients,
    staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1000, // 5 minutes for relatively static data
    gcTime: 10 * 60 * 1000, // Keep in cache for 10 minutes
  });
}

// For real-time data
export function useAttendances(date: string) {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ["attendances", date],
    queryFn: () => getAttendances(date),
    staleTime: 0, // Always check for updates
    refetchInterval: 30000, // Refetch every 30 seconds
  });
}
```

### Request Deduplication

React Query automatically deduplicates requests with the same queryKey. Use this:

```typescript
// Multiple components can call this - only one request made
const { data } = usePatients();
```

### Prefetching

```typescript
// Prefetch data before navigation
const queryClient = useQueryClient();

function prefetchPatient(id: number) {
  queryClient.prefetchQuery({
    queryKey: ["patient", id],
    queryFn: () => getPatient(id),
  });
}
```

## Zustand Performance

### Selective Subscriptions

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Only re-renders when selectedDate changes
const selectedDate = useAttendanceStore((state) => state.selectedDate);

// ❌ WRONG: Re-renders on ANY store change
const store = useAttendanceStore();
const { selectedDate } = store; // Don't destructure entire store
```

### Computed Values in Selectors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Compute derived state in selector
const hasUnsavedChanges = useAttendanceStore((state) =>
  state.attendances.some((a) => a.modified)
);

// ❌ WRONG: Computing in component causes re-renders
const attendances = useAttendanceStore((state) => state.attendances);
const hasUnsavedChanges = attendances.some((a) => a.modified);
```

## React Memoization

### useMemo for Expensive Calculations

```typescript
// ✅ Use for expensive computations
const sortedAndFiltered = useMemo(() => {
  return data.filter(complexFilter).sort(complexSort).map(complexTransform);
}, [data]);

// ❌ Don't use for simple operations
const doubled = useMemo(() => count * 2, [count]); // Overkill
```

### useCallback for Stable References

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Stable callback for child components
const handleClick = useCallback(
  (id: number) => {
    updateItem(id);
  },
  [updateItem]
);

// Pass to memoized children
<MemoizedChild onClick={handleClick} />;
```

### React.memo for Pure Components

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Memo for components that re-render often with same props
export const PatientCard = memo(({ patient }: Props) => {
  return <div>{patient.name}</div>;
});

// ❌ WRONG: Don't memo everything - it has overhead
export const SimpleText = memo(({ text }: Props) => <span>{text}</span>);
```

## Bundle Analysis

Check bundle size regularly:

```bash
npm run analyze        # Generate bundle analysis
npm run bundle-size    # Quick size check
```

Review:

- Large dependencies (consider alternatives)
- Duplicate code (consolidate)
- Unused exports (remove)

### Performance Monitoring

Use bundle analysis and React DevTools Profiler when a change affects a route, list, or modal that renders often.

## Anti-Patterns (Avoid)

❌ **Don't inline large objects in JSX**

```typescript
// WRONG
<Component
  config={
    {
      /* large object */
    }
  }
/>;

// RIGHT
const config = useMemo(
  () => ({
    /* large object */
  }),
  []
);
<Component config={config} />;
```

❌ **Don't create functions in render**

```typescript
// WRONG
<button onClick={() => handleClick(id)}>

// RIGHT
const handleButtonClick = useCallback(() => handleClick(id), [id]);
<button onClick={handleButtonClick}>
```

❌ **Don't subscribe to entire Zustand store**

```typescript
// WRONG
const store = useMyStore();

// RIGHT
const value = useMyStore((state) => state.value);
```

